The paper focuses on evaluating projection techniques for dynamic/temporal data, which involves visualizing and analyzing multidimensional data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Graphics (cs.GR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). However, since the paper primarily deals with the design and evaluation of visualization techniques, we can assume that cs.HC is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because they involve techniques and methods that are used in the paper, such as machine learning algorithms and computer vision techniques.
